        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2018-03-15 07:26:42.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Finally block gives us the opportunity to do some cleanup at the\n > end of the exception handling.Use finally can ensure that our\n > resources are cleaned up\n\nwe can use the finally block, but as we are only closing the resources in that, we can ignore finally as in a try-with-resources statement, any catch or finally block is run after the resources declared have been closed.\nhttps://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/essential/exceptions/tryResourceClose.html",
        "patchset_number": 1
